                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p rend=\"align(right)\"><placeName>Richmond</placeName>\n                                        <date>April 17. 1852</date>.</p>\n                              <p>\n                                        <addressee>Revd Isaac Leeser</addressee>\n                              </p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(1)\">Valued Friend!</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(2)\">If I am not mistaken<lb/> I am indebted to you a\n                                        reply to your<lb/> esteemed favour of the <date>12th\n                                                  March</date>, the con-<lb/>tents of which was duly\n                                        noted, and in reply<lb/> regret that any act of mine should\n                                        have<lb/> proven any wise detrimental to your interest,<lb/>\n                                        I know (that your good knowledge of) Ger-<lb/>man (Bavarian)\n                                        liberality in patronizing a<lb/> Journal could not have been\n                                        much im-<lb/>paired by the publication of the article\n                                        con-<lb/>cerning the \"Beth Haim\" I can assure<lb/> you that\n                                        it did not make one jot<lb/> difference. I have noticed all\n                                        your<lb/> hints concerning the congregation and hope<lb/> to\n                                        profit by them.</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(1)\">I see by the letter that <persName>Jacob A.\n                                                  Levy</persName><lb/> recd from you the other day,\n                                        that you<lb/> anticipate a flare up with the Education<lb/>\n                                        Society, whilst I know that you main-<lb/>tain correct views\n                                        and a stickler of<lb/> just principles, I must advise you,\n                                        to<lb/> desist the opposition to the majority,<lb/> rather\n                                        retire <sic>peacably</sic> from them than<lb/> to combat\n                                        with your superior in power,</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3tt4gd1w/canvas/p1"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
