                {
                  "id": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3tt4gd1w/manifest/annotation/p2",
                  "type": "Annotation",
                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p>I wish I could see you otherwise situated<lb/> with the Israelites\n                                        of <placeName>Philada</placeName>. I fear from<lb/> what I\n                                        can learn that the breach of<lb/>\n                                        <sic>dissention</sic> is expanding between you and<lb/>\n                                        them. I have stuck to your views and<lb/> opposition here\n                                        and would that I was a<lb/> member of \"Mickval Israel\" to\n                                        stand<lb/> by you there.</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(1)\">Our new Hefra are about getting<lb/>\n                                        <persName>Isaac Lyon</persName> to print their constitution\n                                        and<lb/> it will require some Hebrew type, but<lb/> he has a\n                                        parcel a proof of which I en-<lb/>close with the size of the\n                                        type, they lack<lb/> the <add>ן, ץ, ף, ך, ם, ל, ט</add> to\n                                        wit the <add>ל</add><lb/>\n                                        <add>ט</add> all the final letters and the stops<lb/> I\n                                        should like you to send me about<lb/> 12 of each of the\n                                        above if you can<lb/> get them which will complete the lot<lb/>\n                                        <persName>Mr Lyons</persName> has in case you cannot<lb/>\n                                        get them, he wants you to get a<lb/> small font of <hi\n                                                  rend=\"underline\">small pica</hi> say to the<lb/>\n                                        amount of two or three dollars, if<lb/> you can get the size\n                                        like the sample<lb/> he would rather have them, whatever<lb/>\n                                        <sic>expence</sic> may attend the execution of<lb/> this\n                                        order <persName>Mr Mailert</persName> will forward<lb/> to\n                                        you, nothing more but remain as<lb/> ever yours truly</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(2)\">\n                                        <persName role=\"author\">Jacob Ezekiel</persName>\n                              </p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3tt4gd1w/canvas/p2"
                }
              ]
            }
